comments: Thompson (GSW) brings his left forearm toward Brown's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs with Brown's front as he releases away from the lane line.

Thompson (GSW) moves alongside Brown's (BOS) path and marginal body contact occurs at the end of the drive. Thompson's left arm then moves forward and marginal contact occurs with Brown's (BOS) head/neck. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Looney (GSW) closes out the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Horford's (BOS) right arm and slightly extended right leg after the release.
Smart (BOS) and Green (GSW) engage and disengage with one another as the long rebound bounces toward the corner.
Tatum (BOS) briefly has his arms around Looney's (GSW) upper half and quickly releases.
Wiggins (GSW) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage with one another in the corner.
Tatum (BOS) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Wiggins (GSW) moves forward slightly toward Tatum (BOS) and marginal body contact occurs at the end of Tatum's drive.
Tatum's (BOS) momentum continues to carry him forward after he releases the pass and incidental body contact occurs with Looney (GSW) as Looney moves toward the corner.
Horford's (BOS) left foot remains in bounds after he receives the pass.
White (BOS) brings a hand and forearm toward Curry's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs with Curry's front as Curry accelerates toward the top of the perimeter.
Tatum (BOS) is drawn into the air toward Curry (GSW) and marginal body contact occurs as Curry releases the pass.
Looney (GSW) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Smart (BOS) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Green (GSW) engages and disengages with Horford (BOS) during rebounding.
Horford (BOS) brings his left forearm toward Looney's (GSW) back and marginal contact occurs during Looney's upward shooting motion.
Thompson (GSW) and Brown (BOS) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Brown (BOS) is already mishandling the ball in the lane prior to incidental arm contact being made by Wiggins (GSW).
Thompson (GSW) moves forward slightly toward Brown (BOS) and marginal body contact occurs along the sideline prior to Brown losing control of the ball.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Brown (BOS) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Smart (BOS) moves forward toward Curry (GSW) and marginal body contact occurs as Curry receives the pass near the sideline.

Brown (BOS) brings his left arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Curry's (GSW) right arm in the backcourt. After this initial contact, Brown and Curry then make incidental leg-to-leg contact with one another.

Replay review of the foul called on Horford (BOS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Horford turns into Curry (GSW) and initiates contact with Curry's side/left forearm during the driving shot attempt.
Thompson (GSW) brings his right hand forward as he defends the pass and marginal contact occurs with Brown's (BOS) right arm as Brown receives the ball.
Curry (GSW) legally contests White's (BOS) jump shot attempt and he makes incidental contact with White's left hand after the release that does not affect his ability to follow through.
Curry (GSW) keeps his hand on the side of the ball in between dribbles near half-court.
Brown (BOS) slightly extends forward toward Curry (GSW) and marginal contact occurs with Curry's front as he passes the ball along the sideline.
Brown (BOS) and Poole (GSW) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Smart (BOS) turns toward Curry (GSW) and marginal contact occurs with Curry's side/arm after he receives the pass.
Curry (GSW) leans towards Smart (BOS) and the contact is marginal and does not dislodge Smart from his defensive position.
Horford (BOS) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Green (GSW) brings his left hand up and marginal contact occurs with Tatum's (BOS) left shoulder as the rebound falls over Tatum's head.
Brown (BOS) extends his right leg into Curry's (GSW) path and initiates contact with Curry's lower body as he starts his dribble.
